    "Significant treatment effects were followed by two-sample t-tests (two-tailed), comparing all factor levels.",
    "Similar to study 1, Cohen's d is reported as a measure of effect size.",
    "Furthermore, we calculated a binomial logistic regression of the decision to press the \"save link\" button (yes / no), using the author label condition (Human, AI, Human + AI) as a fixed factor and the individual participant as a random factor (intercept).",
    "The author label condition was dummy coded with the \"Human\" condition as the reference category.",
    "P-values were calculated using Satterthwaite's method."
